    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Repairing the System Of Local Governance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas C McMillan letter backs November 23 Soapbox essay on streamlining New Jersey government</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was delighted to see the Nov. 23 Soapbox essay list so many of my favorite complaints about New Jersey's fractured system of governance. Since there are so many deeply entrenched interests that would be adversely affected, it is very doubtful that any of us now living will see the day that these revolutionary changes are brought to fruition. But we can dream, can't we?</p>
        <p>Thomas C. McMillan  Old Bridge</p>
      </block>
